  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a large drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>paneer cubes</strong> and cook for 3-5 min until golden, turning occasionally for even colouring</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the paneer is cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until soft and starting to caramelise</p><p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>crushed cardamom</strong> and <strong>basmati rice</strong> and stir to fully coat the grains</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the softened onion and cook for a further 5-8 min or until starting to brown, stirring occasionally</p><p>While the vegetables are browning, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan and stir until the vegetables are coated</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519__step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519__step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519__step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519__step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519__step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>stir for 1 min, then return the <strong>golden</strong> <strong>paneer</strong> to the pan with the <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered for 5-10 min or until the tomatoes have broken down and the sauce has reduced to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>paneer</strong> <strong>jalfrezi</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding some <strong>pepper</strong> if you like it hot</p><p>Fluff the<strong> basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> with a fork and stir in a knob of <strong>butter</strong> – this is your<strong> cardamom rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/519.step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>paneer jalfrezi</strong> with the<strong> cardamom rice</strong> to the side (watch out for the cardamom pods!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
